---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { buildRetailLink } from "../utils/affiliate";

const clubs = ["Arsenal", "Liverpool", "Manchester United", "Chelsea", "Manchester City", "Barcelona", "Real Madrid", "Bayern Munich", "Inter Milan", "Juventus"];
const clubLinks = clubs.map((club) => {
  const query = `${club} football shirt retro classic`;
  const direct = `https://www.ebay.co.uk/sch/i.html?_nkw=${encodeURIComponent(query)}&_sacat=0&LH_TitleDesc=0`;
  return { club, link: buildRetailLink(direct, import.meta.env.PUBLIC_EBAY_AFFILIATE_LINK_TEMPLATE, query, `shirt-guide-${club.toLowerCase().replaceAll(" ", "-")}`) };
});
const cfsDirect = "https://www.classicfootballshirts.co.uk/";
const vfsDirect = "https://www.vintagefootballshirts.com/";
const cfsLink = buildRetailLink(cfsDirect, import.meta.env.PUBLIC_CFS_AFFILIATE_LINK_TEMPLATE, "classic football shirts", "shirt-guide-cfs");
const vfsLink = buildRetailLink(vfsDirect, import.meta.env.PUBLIC_VFS_AFFILIATE_LINK_TEMPLATE, "vintage football shirts", "shirt-guide-vfs");
const hasAffiliateLinks = [cfsLink, vfsLink, ...clubLinks.map(({ link }) => link)].some((link) => link.isAffiliate);

const schema = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  headline: "Where to buy classic and retro football shirts",
  description: "A practical guide to buying current, classic and retro football shirts safely, including condition, sizing and authenticity checks.",
  mainEntityOfPage: "https://lastseason.co.uk/football-shirts/",
  author: { "@type": "Organization", name: "Last Season" },
  publisher: { "@type": "Organization", name: "Last Season" },
});
---

<Base
  title="Where to Buy Classic & Retro Football Shirts"
  description="A practical guide to buying classic and retro football shirts: retailer options, authenticity checks, sizing, condition and searches for popular clubs."
  canonical="/football-shirts/"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><span class="current">Football shirts</span></nav>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <h1>Where to buy classic and retro football shirts</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Find the shirt you remember, then check it carefully before you buy.</p>
    </section>

    <aside class="commerce-disclosure">
      {hasAffiliateLinks
        ? "Disclosure: some retailer links on this page are affiliate links. Last Season may receive a commission at no extra cost to you."
        : "Retailer links on this page are ordinary outbound links. Last Season currently receives no commission from them."}
    </aside>

    <article class="prose section buying-guide">
      <h2>Start with the exact season</h2>
      <p>A club name and the word “retro” usually produce a very broad search. Add the season, manufacturer and home, away or third to narrow it down. Sponsor names are especially useful when a design was reused across more than one campaign. The <a href="/kits/">Last Season kit colour archive</a> can help identify the era, but its illustrations are colour studies rather than authenticated reproductions.</p>

      <h2>Choose the right type of seller</h2>
      <div class="retailer-grid">
        <a href={cfsLink.url} rel={`${cfsLink.isAffiliate ? "sponsored " : ""}nofollow noopener`} target="_blank" data-retailer="classic-football-shirts" data-commerce-context="shirt-guide-cfs" data-affiliate={String(cfsLink.isAffiliate)}><strong>Classic Football Shirts</strong><span>Specialist catalogue of current and vintage shirts</span></a>
        <a href={vfsLink.url} rel={`${vfsLink.isAffiliate ? "sponsored " : ""}nofollow noopener`} target="_blank" data-retailer="vintage-football-shirts" data-commerce-context="shirt-guide-vfs" data-affiliate={String(vfsLink.isAffiliate)}><strong>Vintage Football Shirts</strong><span>Specialist retro and classic shirt retailer</span></a>
      </div>
      <p>Specialist retailers are useful when you want structured grading and a curated catalogue. Marketplaces can offer more choice and lower prices, but the buyer must assess the individual seller, photographs and description.</p>

      <h2>Popular club shirt searches</h2>
      <div class="club-searches">
        {clubLinks.map(({ club, link }) => (
          <a href={link.url} rel={`${link.isAffiliate ? "sponsored " : ""}nofollow noopener`} target="_blank" data-retailer="ebay" data-commerce-context={`shirt-guide-${club.toLowerCase().replaceAll(" ", "-")}`} data-affiliate={String(link.isAffiliate)}>{club} shirts <span>&rarr;</span></a>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2>Five checks before buying</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Ask for label photographs.</strong> Product codes, wash labels and manufacturer details are more useful than one front-facing image.</li>
        <li><strong>Compare measurements.</strong> Vintage sizing varies. Use the seller's pit-to-pit and length measurements instead of relying only on the size on the tag.</li>
        <li><strong>Inspect the sponsor and printing.</strong> Cracking, lifting, replacement lettering and heat damage materially affect condition and value.</li>
        <li><strong>Read the condition description.</strong> Check for pulls, bobbling, stains, repairs and missing labels, and keep copies of the listing photographs.</li>
        <li><strong>Use protected payment.</strong> Review seller history and use the marketplace or retailer's supported checkout and returns process.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Original, remake or inspired design?</h2>
      <p>An original period shirt, an officially licensed remake and an unofficial reproduction are different products. A trustworthy listing should make that distinction clear. If the price appears unusually low for a rare shirt, treat that as a reason to ask more questions rather than proof of a bargain.</p>
      <p>Last Season does not authenticate shirts and cannot verify a third-party listing. Retailer availability, prices and policies can change, so confirm the details on the seller's site before purchasing.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .commerce-disclosure { margin: 0 0 1.5rem; padding: .85rem 1rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; background: var(--accent-light); font-size: .9rem; }
  .buying-guide { max-width: 900px; }
  .retailer-grid, .club-searches { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(230px, 1fr)); gap: .75rem; margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem; }
  .retailer-grid a, .club-searches a { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: .75rem; padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; text-decoration: none; background: var(--surface); color: var(--text); }
  .retailer-grid a { flex-direction: column; }
  .retailer-grid span { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: .88rem; }
  .retailer-grid a:hover, .club-searches a:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
</style>
